deactivate between beats. This results in an instantaneous
jump in the current when the next stimulus is applied. The
resulting greater repolarizing current acts to shorten APD.
Beyond these initial beats, the magnitude of the instanta-
neous current does not increase, but APD continues to
shorten. This is due to the gradual rise in [Na1]i. The slow
accumulation of [Na1]i alters the behavior of several Na1-
