difference in the [Ca21]i transient is secondary to the dif-
ference in [Na1]i that is imposed (clamped) before the
pacing stimulus. Two sources of Ca21 entry that signifi-
cantly contribute to triggering SR release are the L-type
Ca21 channels and reverse-mode Na1–Ca21 exchanger. As
can be seen in Fig. 7, C and D, the current through these
